Simple C daemon to control mplayer via slave mode protocol

Connect to the daemon on port (default) 7400 and type help
for more information


Installation
	- Download this tar.gz
	- Unzip (which you probably already did!)
	- make
	- optional make install
	- edit /etc/mplayerd.conf

Usage:
	mplayerd

	telnet localhost 7400


Report Bugs to mplayerd-bugs@signuts.net



mplayerd
daemon to control mplayer via TCP/IP

-h --help             Print this help message
-fg --foreground      Don't fork
-p --port port        Specify port, default 7400
-l --logfile file     Log to file default off
-v --version          display version
-d --debug	      specify debug level


DEBUG LEVELS
	0 (no debugging info)
		- client connections and disconnects

	1
		- client send/recv buffers

	2
		- mplayer message thread debug
		- various developer debugging

